  "prompt": "Why I don't get any answer on my question?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're not getting an answer to your question. Here are some possible explanations:\n\n### 1. **Ambiguity or Lack of Clarity:**\n   - If your question is unclear or too vague, people might not understand what you're asking. Try rephrasing it to be more specific and detailed.\n\n### 2. **Complexity:**\n   - If your question is highly complex or requires specialized knowledge, it might take more time for someone with the right expertise to respond.\n\n### 3. **Platform or Context:**\n   - If you're asking on a specific platform (like a forum, social media, or Q&A site), the activity level and audience of that platform could affect whether you get a response. Some platforms might not have the right audience for your question.\n\n### 4. **Time of Posting:**\n   - The time you posted your question might affect visibility. If you posted during a time when fewer people are active, it might take longer to get a response.\n\n### 5. **Overlooked or Buried:**\n   - On busy platforms, your question might get buried under newer posts. Try bumping it up (if allowed) or reposting it at a different time.\n\n### 6. **Lack of Interest or Knowledge:**\n   - Sometimes, the question might not interest the community, or the people who see it might not have the knowledge to answer it.\n\n### 7. **Rules or Restrictions:**\n   - Some platforms have rules that might prevent your question from being seen or answered. For example, certain questions might be against community guidelines.\n\n### 8. **Technical Issues:**\n   - There could be a technical problem with the platform where you posted your question, preventing it from being seen or answered.\n\n### 9. **Patience:**\n   - It might just take some time for someone to come across your question and provide an answer.\n\nIf you still need help, feel free to share your question here, and I\u2019ll do my best to assist you!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
